      "side": 1,
      "message": "So I can load the mailmap only once, and if it changes later, there\u0027s no way to pick up those changes? Doesn\u0027t look very useful to me.\n\nCan we do away with caching the parsed mailmap here, and instead make sure we load it only once in the commands that need it? (Currently BlameResult will call getMailmap() once for each commit produced by the generator, so it relies on this caching here.)\n\nDoes this even belong into the Repository class? Perhaps having a factory method Mailmap.get(Repository repo) would be better?",
      "revId": "7259806da11f461ef7a21897ff34ffdd10d1e1f5",
      "serverId": "d5d70762-12d0-45a1-890d-524b12d3f735"
    },
